    ‚Ä¢	Intrusive Thoughts: Repetitive and distressing thoughts or images that are difficult to control.
    ")
  end

  card StrBehavioral, then: StrSymptoms do
    text("Behavioral Symptoms:
    ‚Ä¢	Changes in Eating Patterns: Stress can lead to overeating or loss of appetite.
    ‚Ä¢	Increased Use of Substances: Escalating use of alcohol, tobacco, or drugs as a way to cope.
    ‚Ä¢	Social Withdrawal: Avoiding social interactions and isolating oneself from friends and family.
    ‚Ä¢	Procrastination: Delaying tasks and responsibilities due to feeling overwhelmed.
    ‚Ä¢	Restlessness: Fidgeting, pacing, or an inability to relax due to inner tension.
    ")
  end

  card StrInterpersonal, then: StrSymptoms do
    text("Interpersonal Symptoms:
    ‚Ä¢	Conflict in Relationships: Increased arguments and disagreements with friends, family, or colleagues.
    ‚Ä¢	Difficulty in Communication: Struggling to express thoughts and feelings clearly, leading to misunderstandings.
    ")
  end

  # Stress6
  card StrMyths do
    list("Choose one to see its fact",
      StrMyth1: "Stress is Always Bad",
      StrMyth2: "Only Major Life Events Cause Stress",
      StrMyth3: "Stress Affects Everyone the Same Way",
      StrMyth4: "Stress Only Affects Mental Health",
